file_content.text: Each of us can carry a handful of fingerling eggs. Once our young destroy the shield generator, we can proceed inside.
How can we help?
The nest will prevail.
If we don't stop the nest, they'll overrun House Cortess!
It's time we found Baroness Chay.
The fingerlings have ruined the power generators. We should find Baroness Chay.
Let's get to the power generators. We have eggs to deliver.
The power generators are behind the main estate. They're well-guarded, but they might be sabotaged from the inside.
If we--if I--could reach the generators, I could release a swarm of fingerling Killiks. Our smallest brethren can easily slip through the cracks and damage the machinery.
Are you any good in a fight?
Can you handle yourself?
The Diplomatic Service taught us basic combat. Our transformation into Dawn Herald enhanced our physical performance. We can hold our own.
You've got miniature saboteur bugs.
Very clever.
Yes. There are times when smaller bodies prove useful.
That's... disgusting.
Ick.
Be that as it may, we believe it's our best chance.
If you two are taking out the shield generators, I'll keep the Cortess patrols busy. Maybe poach something nice.
We'll meet up after this is over.
Understood.
You and Bugboy have a good time.
You planning to steal the baron's prize thrantas?
Poaching, huh?
What? We've got room on the ship.
Keep out of trouble--this is a delicate situation.
Don't mess things up.
Anything you say, mom.
Anything you say, papa.
Brrru urub burr.
Agent! Come inside--the nest is prepared to defend you.
Yeah. That's what you need these bugs for. Defending us.
Our observers saw what happened. Why did Cortess turn on you? How can we help?
The Cortess estate has activated their defense systems. What's going on?
Turns out the baroness is working with the terrorists.
Denri Ayl was their ally.
The baroness? This is... unexpected.
Cortess knows I'm coming after them.
They're preparing for me.
We won't pretend to understand--but we'll assist however we can.
You're not authorized for that information.
Not your concern.
Acknowledged. But you're here, so we'll assist if we can.
The nest has studied the Cortess estate's defenses and deemed them formidable.
The interior shields are designed for squads of human attackers. The perimeter security systems are meant to combat armies--and Killik swarms.
Can we disable the shields somehow?
Recommendations?
Why does the nest know so much about Cortess defenses?
You're awfully well-informed.
We've been studying Cortess for some time. We've been thorough.
Give me something I can use, Vector.
That's not helpful.
We're working on it.
We're certain Denri Ayl will not escape you.
This is... perplexing. It looks like Ayl funded the destruction of the Dominator and the assassination of Darth Jadus....
... but the rest is very odd. Have you shown this to Baron Peyar?
I was hoping I wouldn't need to.
I'm a bit reluctant.
Baron Peyar may see nuances we don't. We've mentioned our difficulty with human personalities.
He's my next stop.
Of course. We appreciate being kept apprised--we know you're under no obligation.
Can't you handle one simple task?
That's your best advice?
Respectfully, we've been with you this entire venture. If you're displeased, report it to our superiors.
We'll be on alert, should you need anything else. The nest embraces our unity.
Agent, it's good to see you.
Burru urrub bu!
Yes. We...
Urr rurr ub!
We apologize. The nest has been invigorated by Star-Dancing. If you could smell the pheromones, you'd understand our restlessness.
Having trouble controlling the Killiks?
Your friends seem excited.
This restlessness--is it going to be a problem?
Should I be worried?
If I start "understanding," I'll know it's time to leave.
I can do without.
There's nothing to be concerned about; the hive is growing, and we all benefit. We even have a gift for you.
These orbs contain white membrosia--rare nectar produced by our Givers. Pull back the wax and sip; you'll find it gives strength and healing.
Practical, but exotic--I like it.
Very nice.
We hoped you might.
Nothing wins a girl's heart like bug milk.
You know how to treat a woman.
There's truth to that among Killiks--but we're not sure you'd like the details.
Mass-produce these, and we can make a fortune.
I wonder what it'd sell for?
Once the nest expands, we'll consider a proposal.
You're sure it's safe for humans?
It looks dangerous.
The membrosia alone won't make you a Joiner--in these quantities.
In any case, how's the search for Denri Ayl?
Here--I located the files in House Alde.
It's going very well.
I found records in the Alde estate, but I'm not sure what to make of them.
Mixed.
Take a look at these files. What do you think?
You tell me.
We recommend that you visit House Alde. It's the best way of locating our terrorist financier.
Our observers saw you enter the Cortess estate. The fingerlings were listening, and heard mention of Denri Ayl.
We met Ayl during our time as ambassador. With his wealth and talent, he could be your target.
The baron claims not to know his whereabouts.
He's also missing.
We might be able to help.
Oh?
Denri Ayl could obtain funding from houses across Alderaan. He could supply a terrorist army. We think we can find him.
I don't need your opinion, Vector. Just follow my orders.
Did I ask for your analysis?
We didn't mean to overstep our bounds. Still, we have a thought.
Our nest has had many Joiners over the years--soldiers. Children. Nobles.
We can search their memories and see what they know of Denri Ayl.
Let's see what you come up with.
Get to it.
Are all these people in the nest like you?
Other Joiners?
As Dawn Herald and emissary to the Empire, we retain more independence. But we're all Joiners.
You just go through people's brains?
That's monstrous.
The Joiners are already part of the nest. They share thoughts willingly. Don't be concerned.
Urrub bu uru.
We remember Pabel Alde. When her speeder crashed, our foragers brought her to the hive. Our healers tended her. We became one.
Burrr ururr ur.
Her house. House Alde--an old house, of scholars and antiquarians--granted Ayl residence in honor of his work as a mediator.
Ayl kept records of his work in the Alde estate. If you can penetrate the estate's defenses, those records are yours.
Good work. I'll have those records in no time.
Consider it done.
If we may be so bold, a warning:
I've never seen anything quite like that.
That was very strange.
We live to serve.
You say "penetrate their defenses." What about a diplomatic approach?
Is violence necessary?
It's unlikely to work.
House Alde opposes the Empire, and the estate is always prepared for an Imperial attack--even a stealthy one. Be careful.
Urrub. Bu urr ruburr.
Is it me, or are there more bugs than last time?
Welcome back. Your aura reflects your attunement to the great Song.
Vector. Good to see you again, too.
Always a pleasure.
What are all these Killiks doing here?
Why so many bugs?
The hive requires more nutrients. These are foraging parties; they'll gather what we need.
Are you short on supplies?
Why are you foraging?
We've been depleting resources rapidly this season--but our foragers can compensate.
Cortess isn't happy about having Killiks around, you know.
You're upsetting the nobles.
Yes. We apologize for the incident with the battle droids. It should've been avoided.
The foraging can wait until my mission is done.
No. Keep the Killiks inside.
Burr ubb. Urbur urr ruburr.
The nest requires more nutrients. We apologize, but we can't delay.
I'm not interested in alien babble.
Cut the gibberish.
Of course. You're here to work.
We cannot help you further. Seek the Cortess baron.
Burruburr uru bu. Burrub.
Yes. This is the one, as the song-schedule determined.
I can't wait to see how this goes.
We are Vector Hyllus, Dawn Herald of the Oroboro nest. Pleased to make your acquaintance, agent.
Cipher Nine. I'm with Imperial Intelligence.
Hello, there.
Of course.
It sounds like you were expecting me.
You know who I am?
We received a message concerning your mission. We were told we might serve.
You must be the man with a bug for a brain.
I hear you're some freak.
We must be. We're glad you were briefed.
We trust our appearance doesn't disturb you? Our superiors in the Diplomatic Service find our Joining disconcerting--but it was necessary.
The Joining allowed us to share thoughts and senses with the nest--forge a bond between Empire and Killiks. The change is a small price.
Being transformed doesn't bother you?
A small price?
It was unexpected, but now... I'm part of the Kind. I hear the Song of the Universe. It's a magnificent thing.
Changed or not, you clean up well.
[Flirt] You look pretty good.
You're very kind. We'd rub forearms, but it might not translate.
So long as it gets the job done.
I'm not bothered.
We appreciate your professionalism.
I just came for information. Your personal life is your own business.
I'm really not interested.
I understand. The Killiks will help; together, we have millennia of experience.
Burru. Ubu urr rurr.
Yes. As to your target--Imperial Intelligence provided us with a list of names, dates and locations connected to your terrorist financier.
Do you have an ID on the target?
What have you found out?
I'm waiting.
I'm not sure I like sharing information with the Killiks.
That's confidential data.
It's unavoidable. Our thoughts are shared. Perhaps you'll make the best of it.
We can't identify the financier himself, but your information shows he's visited House Organa, House Serrus, House Panteer... and House Cortess.
Cortess is a vassal of the Empire's proxy--House Thul. If you show the Cortess baron a copy of our findings, he might close in on your foe.
If I can manipulate a Hutt, I can handle a baron.
Sounds easy enough.
A Hutt? Indeed.
Noted.
I was hoping for a more solid lead.
I'm not convinced.
So were we.
We must proceed to the Dance of Unlighting, but we'll remain here for the duration of your mission.
We suggest you present yourself to Cortess as an ally of the Empire. Show strength... and don't mention your Intelligence connections.
These are the lands of the Oroboro nest. We will not permit intruders.
We regret to say we can't help you.
